---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro'
import BackButton from '../../../components/BackButton.astro'
import DescriptionCard from '../../../components/DescriptionCard.astro'
import CodePreviewCard from '../../../components/CodePreviewCard.astro'
import DescriptionCardHeader from '../../../components/DescriptionCardHeader.astro'
import DescriptionCardText from '../../../components/DescriptionCardText.astro'
import DownloadButton from '../../../components/DownloadButton.astro'
---

<Layout title="JS Cheat Sheet | Template">
    <BackButton className="back-button" id="back_button" href="/second_semester/" buttonText="Back to overview"/>

    <div class="container desc-container">
        <DescriptionCard class="card what-card">
            <div class="card what-card">
                <DescriptionCardHeader class="what-header" headerText="Template"/>

                <DescriptionCardText>
                    <span class="element">Template</span> is an HTML <span class="element">element</span> working as a placeholder for some content generated by JavaScript. The content can't therefore be seen, before it has been generated by JavaScript.
                    To get the content to show up, a couple of different <span class="method">methods</span> are needed, namely <span class="method">.cloneNode<span class="parentheses">()</span></span> og <span class="method">.append</span><span class="parentheses">()</span> eller <span class="method">.appendChild</span><span class="parentheses">()</span> samt <span class="property">.content</span>. What that looks like can be found in the downloadable example
                    <DownloadButton
                        href="/zips/template-eksempel.zip"
                        class="btn zip-file-download-btn"
                        id="zip_file_download_btn"
                        download="template-eksempel"
                    >
                    here.
                </DescriptionCardText>
            </div>
        </DescriptionCard>

        <DescriptionCard class="card syntax-card">
            <div class="card syntax-card">
                <DescriptionCardHeader class="syntax-header" headerText="Syntax" />

                <DescriptionCardText>
                    The syntax is pretty easy, since it consists of an opening and closing <span class="element">element</span> with content - precisely as the majority of the HTML <span class="element">elements</span>. 
                </DescriptionCardText>
            </div>

            <CodePreviewCard>
                <h3>
                    <pre>


                    <span class="element">&lt;template&gt;</span>
                    &nbsp;&nbsp;// Content here
                    <span class="element">&lt;/template&gt;</span>

                    </pre>
                </h3>
            </CodePreviewCard>
        </DescriptionCard>
    </div>
</Layout>

<style>
    h3
    {
        font-size: 22px;
    }
</style>